Ivory Coast’s Government Lifts Cocoa Export Ban, Says Ports to Reopen

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-04-15T10:06:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/ivory-coast-s-government-lifts-cocoa-export-ban-says-ports-to-reopen.html
Ivory Coast ’s government, led by
 Alassane Ouattara , has lifted a ban on cocoa and coffee exports
and said the nation’s ports will reopen this week.  The payment of taxes on cocoa exports will resume, the
government said in an e-mailed response to questions.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  